1.1 a)¶

i)¶

$ \sum _{j=1} p_{j|i} = 1 $

$ p_{j|i} = \frac{e^{-||x_i - x_j||^2 \ / \ 2 \sigma _i^2}}{\sum \limits_{k \neq i} e^{-||x_i - x_k||^2 \ / \ 2 \sigma _i^2}} $

$ 1 = \sum \limits_{j = 1} ^n \frac{e^{-||x_i - x_j||^2 \ / \ 2 \sigma _i^2}}{\sum \limits_{k \neq i} e^{-||x_i - x_k||^2 \ / \ 2 \sigma _i^2}} $ with example points $ \in \{1,2\}, \sigma = 1 $

$ 1 = \frac{e^{-1}}{e^{-1} + e^{-2}} + \frac{e^{-2}}{e^{-1} + e^{-2}} $

$ 1 = 1 $
